    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The squealing sound from your 2018 Toyota Camry, you say? That's a bit of a nagging issue, isn't it? A high-pitched squeal, especially when slowing down or braking at low speeds, is often a sign of worn-out brake pads or warped rotors. It's a bit like a goblin trying to get your attention, but instead of a pesky creature, it's your car's way of telling you that something's amiss. \n\nYou might want to check the brake pads and rotors to see if they're worn out or warped. If they are, it's likely that the squeal will become even louder and more frequent. It's a bit like a goblin's lair – once you know where to look, you'll find the problem. \n\nI'd recommend having a professional mechanic take a closer look, though. They can use specialized tools to diagnose the issue and recommend the best course of action. After all, you don't want to be stuck with a squealing brake system that's causing you more stress than a goblin's mischief.",
